    <div class="content-pane">
      <div class="content-pane-body">
        <h1 id="overview">libTTIO — TTI-O Objective-C Reference Implementation</h1>
        <p>
          libTTIO is the reference implementation of the TTI-O multi-omics data
          standard. It provides Objective-C classes and protocols for authoring,
          reading, querying, encrypting, and signing <code>.tio</code> files
          (HDF5 container format).
        </p>
        <p>
          All classes listed in the left navigation are public API. Cross-language
          equivalents in Python (<code>ttio.*</code>) and Java
          (<code>com.dtwthalion.ttio.*</code>) are documented in the class
          comments where they exist.
        </p>

        <h2 id="classes">Core classes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOSpectralDataset.html#class$TTIOSpectralDataset">TTIOSpectralDataset</a> — top-level container for acquisition runs</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOAcquisitionRun.html#class$TTIOAcquisitionRun">TTIOAcquisitionRun</a> — single LC-MS / NMR run with spectra, chromatograms, identifications</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOMassSpectrum.html#class$TTIOMassSpectrum">TTIOMassSpectrum</a> — mass-spectrum axis (m/z, intensity)</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIONMRSpectrum.html#class$TTIONMRSpectrum">TTIONMRSpectrum</a> — 1D NMR spectrum</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOMSImage.html#class$TTIOMSImage">TTIOMSImage</a> — MS-imaging (MALDI) dataset</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Storage providers</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOHDF5Provider.html#class$TTIOHDF5Provider">TTIOHDF5Provider</a> — canonical HDF5 back-end</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOSqliteProvider.html#class$TTIOSqliteProvider">TTIOSqliteProvider</a> — single-file SQLite back-end (Provisional)</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOMemoryProvider.html#class$TTIOMemoryProvider">TTIOMemoryProvider</a> — in-memory provider for tests</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Protection</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOEncryptionManager.html#class$TTIOEncryptionManager">TTIOEncryptionManager</a> — AES-256-GCM intensity-channel encryption</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOSignatureManager.html#class$TTIOSignatureManager">TTIOSignatureManager</a> — HMAC-SHA256 v2 canonical signatures</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOAccessPolicy.html#class$TTIOAccessPolicy">TTIOAccessPolicy</a> — access-control policy JSON</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOAnonymizer.html#class$TTIOAnonymizer">TTIOAnonymizer</a> — one-shot anonymization</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Import / export</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOMzMLReader.html#class$TTIOMzMLReader">TTIOMzMLReader</a> / <a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOMzMLWriter.html#class$TTIOMzMLWriter">TTIOMzMLWriter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIONmrMLReader.html#class$TTIONmrMLReader">TTIONmrMLReader</a> / <a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIONmrMLWriter.html#class$TTIONmrMLWriter">TTIONmrMLWriter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOISAExporter.html#class$TTIOISAExporter">TTIOISAExporter</a></li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOThermoRawReader.html#class$TTIOThermoRawReader">TTIOThermoRawReader</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="protocols">Domain protocols</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOCVAnnotatable.html#protocol$(TTIOCVAnnotatable)">TTIOCVAnnotatable</a> — controlled-vocabulary annotation</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOEncryptable.html#protocol$(TTIOEncryptable)">TTIOEncryptable</a> — intensity-channel encryption</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOIndexable.html#protocol$(TTIOIndexable)">TTIOIndexable</a> — spectrum-index construction</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOProvenanceable.html#protocol$(TTIOProvenanceable)">TTIOProvenanceable</a> — provenance metadata</li>
          <li><a rel="gsdoc" href="TTIOStreamable.html#protocol$(TTIOStreamable)">TTIOStreamable</a> — streaming read/write</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <em>Every class page carries the full class sidebar on the left. Start
          anywhere.</em>
        </p>
